OL,7,FInquiry chair Sir Brian Langstaff said
OL,8,Fat the time that he "could not in
OL,9,Fconscience add to the decades-long
OL,10,Fdelays" victims had already faced.
OL,12,FSome people have already received
OL,13,Finterim payments of #100,000, but Sir
OL,14,FBrian said that a number have gone
OL,15,F"unrecognised" ` including parents who
OL,16,Flost children and children orphaned
OL,17,Fwhen their parents died ` as he called
OL,18,Ffor the interim scheme to be extended.
