OL,7,FThousands of patients were infected
OL,8,Fwith HIV and hepatitis C through
OL,9,Fcontaminated blood and blood products
OL,10,Fin the 1970s and 1980s, in what has
OL,11,Fbeen dubbed the worst treatment
OL,12,Fdisaster in the history of the NHS.
OL,14,FRichard Angell, chief executive of
OL,15,FTerrence Higgins Trust, described
OL,16,FApril 5 as "another grim anniversary
OL,17,Ffor those infected and affected by the
OL,18,Fcontaminated blood scandal".
OL,26,@xD@LOUzD@[O]
