OL,7,FHe added: "Precisely one year ago, the
OL,8,Finquiry's chair Sir Brian Langstaff
OL,9,Fpublished his second interim report
OL,10,Fstating clearly that parents and
OL,11,Fchildren who suffered bereavements as
OL,12,Fa result of the scandal should receive
OL,13,F#100,000 in interim compensation.
OL,15,F"He did this to try and alleviate
OL,16,Fimmediate suffering, saying that
OL,17,Fdelaying recommendations on
OL,18,Fcompensation until the final report
OL,19,Fwould cause further harm to people who
OL,20,Fhad already been failed by government.
OL,26,@oD@KOUwD@AOU
