OL,5,Ccharity
OL,7,F"Interim payments have already been
OL,8,Fmade to those infected and bereaved
OL,9,Fpartners, but not parents or children
OL,10,F` despite the devastating impact on
OL,11,Fthem. Including parents who
OL,12,Funknowingly infected their children
OL,13,Fwith contaminated blood products and
OL,14,Fchildren who were orphaned by the
OL,15,Fscandal.
OL,17,F"These people have been waiting half a
OL,18,Fcentury for justice and government
OL,19,Fmustn't drag its feet any longer.
OL,26,@oD@AOUyD@AOU
